creditline: Gift of Elizabeth, Julie, and Catherine Andrus in memory of John and Marion Andrus
description: hunchback with upturned nose, and long feathers on top of head in fencing pose, facing R with two short swords in his hands
provenance: [Pia Gallo, Chicago, until 1986; sold to Andrus]; John E. Andrus III, Wayzata, Minn.; by descent to his daughters, Elizabeth, Katie, and Julie. Earlier provenances have been gathered, but further research will increase our knowledge of their histories.
title: Duelist with Two Sabers
